body:
[
{
"type": "lead",
"text": "10 Marla Grey Structure Cost in Lahore 2026 is one of the most searched construction queries as property owners want clear and updated budgeting before starting their house."
},
{
"type": "heading",
"text": "Introduction"
},
{
"type": "paragraph",
"text": "Construction costs in Lahore are changing due to material rates, labor charges, and design standards. For a 10 marla house, understanding the grey structure cost is the first and most important step before starting any project."
},
{
"type": "heading",
"text": "Average Cost in 2026"
},
{
"type": "paragraph",
"text": "The estimated grey structure cost for a 10 marla house in Lahore in 2026 ranges between 95 lakh to 1.2 crore PKR depending on design, location, and material quality."
},
{
"type": "stats",
"statItems": [
{
"label": "Minimum Cost",
"value": "95 Lakh PKR",
"note": "Basic design with standard materials"
},
{
"label": "Average Cost",
"value": "1.05 Crore PKR",
"note": "Most common construction range"
},
{
"label": "High-End Cost",
"value": "1.2 Crore PKR",
"note": "Premium materials and DHA projects"
}
]
},
{
"type": "heading",
"text": "Per Square Foot Rate"
},
{
"type": "paragraph",
"text": "The per square foot cost for grey structure construction in Lahore is typically between 2,600 to 3,300 PKR depending on material selection and contractor expertise."
},
{
"type": "bullets",
"title": "What affects per sq ft cost",
"bulletItems": [
"Steel and cement price fluctuations",
"Brick quality and availability",
"Labor skill level",
"Design complexity",
"Location such as DHA or Bahria"
]
},
{
"type": "heading",
"text": "What is Included in Grey Structure"
},
{
"type": "bullets",
"title": "Included work",
"bulletItems": [
"Foundation and excavation",
"Brick masonry and structure",
"Roof slabs and concrete work",
"Plumbing and electrical piping",
"Water tanks and basic fittings"
]
},
{
"type": "callout",
"title": "Important Note",
"text": "Choosing the cheapest contractor often leads to hidden costs later. Proper supervision and quality materials are essential for long-term durability."
},
{
"type": "heading",
"text": "DHA vs Other Areas"
},
{
"type": "table",
"tableRows": [
{
"area": "DHA Lahore",
"positioning": "Premium construction zone",
"expectation": "Higher cost but strict quality and better supervision"
},
{
"area": "Bahria Town",
"positioning": "Planned community",
"expectation": "Moderate to high cost with good infrastructure"
},
{
"area": "Other Lahore Areas",
"positioning": "General residential zones",
"expectation": "Lower cost but depends on contractor quality"
}
]
},
{
"type": "heading",
"text": "Conclusion"
},
{
"type": "paragraph",
"text": "A realistic 10 marla grey structure cost in Lahore for 2026 is between 95 lakh to 1.2 crore PKR. Proper planning, experienced supervision, and quality materials are key to a durable and long-lasting home."
},
{
"type": "callout",
"title": "Expert Help",
"text": "For accurate cost estimation and professional construction guidance, consult experienced builders before starting your project."
}
]
